Members of Balsaminaceae have a diverse and elaborately sculptured seed coat. Unfortunately, till now seed morphology has been observed only for a small number of 
 Impatiens species, which has limited the use of the morphological traits of seeds in taxonomy and classification (e.g., 
 Song, Yuan & Kupfer, 2005; 
 Utami & Shimizu, 2005; 
 Chen et al., 2007; 
 Yu, Chen & Qin, 2007; 
 Jin et al., 2008; 
 Shui et al., 2011).
